orian" era="ce" normal="1843/1843">1843</unitdate><container id="aspace_e1393a6c20279cd648ef3be1056d4ddb" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_e00e55f0308e0b6a4e620e9d7e5cea8a" parent="aspace_e1393a6c20279cd648ef3be1056d4ddb" type="folder">17</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_62940ac2599d23a370b4b8062e2b46d4" level="item"><did><unittitle>Tompkins County Election Returns, Nov. 30, 1836-Nov. 22, 1848 . Folder contains returns for various town, county, state, and federal elections held during this period. Articles from <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title> and <title>Ithaca Journal</title>.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1836-11-30/1848-11-22" type="inclusive">Nov. 30, 1836-Nov. 22, 1848</unitdate><container id="aspace_a0feb2f940abb1e35f92f45f80459c12" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_5c81a6238e1b13c15c817e11322c4abf" parent="aspace_a0feb2f940abb1e35f92f45f80459c12" type="folder">18</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_8a7f96942566fca8837cb11c0479e48f" level="item"><did><unittitle>Articles on slavery, abolition, and colonization, Apr. 5, 1837-Apr. 18, 1838. Folder contains assorted articles on the issues surrounding slavery. Articles from <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title> and <title>The Ithaca Journal and Herald</title>.</unittitle><container id="aspace_733a1bb992351fa044eedc9b988f768f" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_643f7ed7533240ac45a8a083c9ce6d66" parent="aspace_733a1bb992351fa044eedc9b988f768f" type="folder">19</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_1c38f12fd9778ac3db661a741f138526" level="item"><did><unittitle>Residents of Tompkins County call meeting to discuss fiscal problems they believe caused by politicians in Albany. Article appears in May 7, 1834 <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title>.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1834-05-07/1834-05-